Since the last digits of the two factors and the product are the same digit $x$, with $0 \leq x \leq 9$, the product of $x$ with itself must also end in $x$.

This is only true for the digits $x=0, x=1, x=5$ and $x=6$. Therefore, the two factors are either 130, 70 or 131, 71 or 135, 75 or 136, 76. The multiplication yields:

$130 \cdot 70=9100$ is four digits and thus not a solution;

$131 \cdot 71=9301$ is four digits and also not a solution;

$135 \cdot 75=10125$ is five digits, but the tens and hundreds places are not the same;

$136 \cdot 76=10336$ meets all the requirements and is therefore the only solution to the problem.

